Mexico Stocks: America Movil, Minera Frisco, Penoles, Soriana

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-06-23T20:45:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/mexico-stocks-america-movil-minera-frisco-penoles-soriana.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The IPC index fell 0.2 percent to 35,326.66.  Silver futures for September delivery tumbled as much as
5.7 percent to $34.66 an ounce on the Comex in New York.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, declined 2.5 percent to 436.68 pesos. Minera
Frisco SAB (MFRISCOA MM), the mining company controlled by
billionaire  Carlos Slim , dropped 1.4 percent to 52.86 pesos.  Mexico’s unemployment rate unexpectedly climbed to 5.2
percent in May, according to the national statistics institute.
Economists forecast a jobless rate of 4.9 percent, according to
the median of 13 estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  Organizacion Soriana SAB (SORIANAB MM), Mexico’s second-
largest grocery store chain, retreated 2 percent to 33.55 pesos.
Wal-Mart de Mexico SAB (WALMEXV MM),  Latin America ’s largest
retailer, fell 0.5 percent to 34.13 pesos.  America Movil  SAB (AMXL MM), the wireless carrier
controlled by Slim, added 0.2 percent to 30.33 pesos. America
Movil had its foreign currency issuer default rating upgraded to
A from A- by  Fitch Ratings  with a stable outlook.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
